data.contentText: Refer to WHO plan A, B or C as below:

metadata.text1:
Give extra fluid orally:
Breastfeed frequently and for longer each feed
If infant vomits, wait 10 minutes then start again
If continues to vomit, will need clinic review
metadata.text2:
Give 75ml/kg over 4 hours orally
Either by frequent breast feeds or cup feeds with EBM/formula
Reassess dehydration after 4 hours and select appropriate plan (A, B, C) to continue. 
If vomits, wait for 10 minutes then continue to offer feeds but more slowly
metadata.text3:
Give iv fluids10% dextrose or Ringers Lactate. 
Give first 30ml/kg in 1 hour, then 70ml/kg in 5 hours. 
Continue to offer breast/ cup feeds as tolerated

Reassess every 1-2 hours. If not improving, increase drip rate and check renal function
Monitor urine output
At 6 hours, reassess dehydration status and continue with plan A, B or C as appropriate

data.title: MANAGEMENT
